The paper discusses a framework for component-based software engineering and model-driven engineering applied to robotics application development. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including software engineering (cs.SE), robotics (cs.RO), programming languages (cs.PL), systems and control (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on architecture description languages and generative development, cs.SE is the most likely category, followed by cs.RO and cs.PL.
